The paper deals with the problem of Answer Quality Prediction (AQP) in Community Question Answering (cQA) forums, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and deep learning (DL) techniques, which suggest possible sub-categories of cs.IR and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that combines hand-crafted features and deep learning, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
